  • Package dempred.datastructure

    • Class dempred.datastructure.Datapoint extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • comment

          java.lang.String comment
          Used for additional information on a datapoint.

        • group

          java.lang.Integer group
          The group of a datapoint for classification tasks (e.g. -1 for negative, +1 for positive datapoints)

        • weight

          double weight
          Can be used to weigh more reliable data points higher than others during learning. OUtliers for example should be weighted lower than other datapoints. E.g. all datapoints weight=1.0 and outliers weight=0.5

        • value

          double value
          The value of the datapoint. For regression tasks this is the value which the classifier tries to predict. For classification tasks 'value' should be set to -1 or +1 for negative and positive datapoints respectively.

        • predictedGroup

          java.lang.Integer predictedGroup
          Contains the predicted group after prediction.

        • predictedValue

          double predictedValue
          Contains predicted value after prediction.

        • featureVector

          FVector featureVector
          The feature vector which contains all descriptors of this datapoint.

        • extended

          boolean extended
          A boolean indicating if this datapoint's featureVector is extendet by an additional value set to 1.0. This is used to encode the bias parameter 'b'

    • Class dempred.datastructure.Dataset extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      6560594683595420293L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          The name of this dataset (e.g. trainset, testset...).

        • comment

          java.lang.String comment
          The comment for this dataset (e.g. source, date...).

        • datapoints

          java.util.List<E> datapoints
          The list of datapoints this dataset contains.

        • groupCounter

          java.util.Map<K,V> groupCounter
          A simple map which contains the number of datapoints for a specific group (e.g. how many negative and how many positive datapoints does this dataset contain).

        • featureIndex

          java.util.List<E> featureIndex
          The feature index. This is a simple index starting from '0' to 'numberOfFeatures-1'. This is a usefull structure if at any point of model building features are deleted. This index will help to keep track which features are still used.

        • featureNames

          java.util.List<E> featureNames
          The feature names. If the used features have names or a description this list should contain these. That way the feature names can be used to identify the features at any stage of model building.
